Twenty-six-year-old Constable Lonwabo Soga was shot while on duty on 3 December. CAPE TOWN – A sixth suspect has been arrested in connection with the murder  of a police officer in Coffee Bay. Twenty-six-year-old Constable Lonwabo Soga was shot while on duty on 3 December. Hawks Spokesperson Anelisa Ngcakani said: “The 27-year-old’s case was remanded to 22 January for legal representation. He will appear together with the five accused, who have been arrested for the murder of Constable Soga.”